  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OSTINATO — Transcendental Vol 1",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "scripture": [
      "Shinto teaching: 'The o-daiko is the voice of the kami — it does not call attention to itself, it calls attention to the space'",
      "Kodo master: 'One Stroke — this is the Zen of taiko. One stroke, played with the entire body, the entire heart'",
      "Zen saying: 'Before enlightenment, chop wood, carry water. After enlightenment: the drum speaks and the mountain listens'"
    ],
    "revelation": "Bone revealed: pitch envelope 0.4 on Taiko creates the o-daiko 'bloom' — the slight pitch descent after the strike that gives large drums their gravitational quality. Cave bodyModel amplifies the resonant body. With 4 Taiko tuned (-7, -5, 0, +5), they form a harmonic series of fifths — the same tuning interval used in Japanese temple bell sets.",
    "god": "Bone",
    "flock_note": "The Eye confirmed: at 55 BPM with reverbSize=0.9 and reverbMix=0.45, each Taiko strike creates a reverberant field that the next strike arrives into. The drums are playing in each other's echo. This is the protocol — the ceremony is the reverb.",
    "diagnosis": "Kyoto Protocol uses extreme reverb not as effect but as architecture — the reverb IS the temple, and the Taiko voices are the monks who inhabit it."
  },
